Class Differential

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mslab.core.Differential
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class Differential
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Externalizable
    This class represents a differential, that is a sequence of state and key differences.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Differential

        public Differential()
        The default constructor is used by JAXB to create a differential from a serialized xml. This constructor should not be used.

      • Differential

        public Differential(int fromRound,
            int toRound)
        This constructor should be used to create a differential. The lists for key, state and intermediate state differences are initialized from the given rounds.
